randoop.types

Class GenericTypeBound

  • java.lang.Object
    • randoop.types.TypeBound
      • randoop.types.GenericTypeBound

  • public class GenericTypeBound
extends TypeBound
    Represents a type bound in which a type variable occurs. To evaluate this kind of bound, a substitution is needed to instantiate the bound to a concrete type bound.
    See Also:
    GenericClassType, Substitution

      • isSatisfiedBy

        public boolean isSatisfiedBy(ConcreteType argType,
                             Substitution substitution)
                      throws RandoopTypeException
        Determines if this is an upper bound for the concrete argument type. This generic type bound is satisfied by a concrete type if the concrete type formed by applying the substitution to this generic bound is satisfied by the concrete type.
        Overrides:
        isSatisfiedBy in class TypeBound
        Parameters:
        argType - the concrete argument type
        Returns:
        true if this bound is satisfied by the concrete type when the substitution is used on the bound, false otherwise
        Throws:
        RandoopTypeException

      • instantiate

        public ConcreteTypeBound instantiate(Substitution substitution)
                              throws RandoopTypeException
        Creates concrete type bound from this bound by instantiating the type variables of this bound with the given substitution. The substitution must be for the generic class to which the bound belongs.
        Parameters:
        substitution - the substitution for instantiating type variables
        Returns:
        the concrete type bound formed by substituting type variables with the concrete types using the substitution
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if either an argument is not a type variable, or a type variable has no instantiation in the substitution
        RandoopTypeException

      • getRuntimeClass

        public java.lang.Class<?> getRuntimeClass()
        Returns the runtime class for this type bound. Depending on implementing class, this may be Object or something closer to the bound. The returned value should not be used to test satisfiability of the bound. As a hack to return something usable, returns Object, but needs to be bound based on parameter.
        Overrides:
        getRuntimeClass in class TypeBound
        Returns:
        the runtime class for this type bound
